paragraph.content:
includes any version of an aircraft described in paragraph (a) that
                    performs specialized electronic warfare, suppression of air defence or
                    reconnaissance missions;

securities and debt instruments (including stocks and shares, certificates
                    representing securities, bonds, notes, warrants, debentures, debenture stock and
                    derivatives contracts);

section.def:
master (船長), in relation
            to a ship, includes any person (other than a pilot) for the time being in charge of the
            ship;

paragraph.content:
any guided or unguided rocket, ballistic or cruise missile or remotely
                    piloted vehicle capable of delivering a warhead or weapon of destruction to a
                    range of at least 25 km;

section.def:
operator (營運人), in
            relation to a ship, aircraft or vehicle, means the person for the time being having the
            management of the ship, aircraft or vehicle;

subparagraph.content:
a body mentioned in paragraph (c) or (d);
                        (L.N. 5 of
                            2010)

paragraph.content:
any supply-sanctioned item;
                    (L.N. 122 of
                    2018)

section.def:
specified item (指明項目) means an item specified in Schedule 2;
            (L.N. 115 of
                2014)

paragraph.content:
a ship that is not registered in the HKSAR and is within the waters of Hong Kong;
                    (L.N. 5 of
                        2010)

an aircraft that is not registered in the HKSAR and is within Hong Kong air space;
                    (L.N. 5 of
                        2010)

for a ship registered in the
                    HKSAR—the
                    charterer, the operator and the master of the ship;

subparagraph.content:
the charterer of the ship, if the charterer is in the HKSAR, or is both
                        a Hong Kong permanent resident and a Chinese national, or is a body
                        incorporated or constituted under the law of the HKSAR;

the charterer of the aircraft, if the charterer is in the HKSAR, or is
                        both a Hong Kong permanent resident and a Chinese national, or is a body
                        incorporated or constituted under the law of the HKSAR;

the pilot in command of the aircraft, if the pilot in command is in the
                        HKSAR or is both a Hong Kong permanent resident and a Chinese
                        national;

paragraph.content:
that the technical training, service, assistance or advice concerned
                    related to the provision, manufacture, maintenance or use of any specified arms;
                    or

that the technical training, service, assistance or advice concerned
                    related to the provision, manufacture, maintenance or use of any specified item;
                    or

for a contravention of subsection (2B)(a)—that the ship
                    concerned was owned, controlled or operated by a person connected with the
                    DPRK;

for a contravention of subsection (2B)(b)—that the ship
                    concerned was involved in an activity prohibited by the Security Council
                    Resolutions;

the provision of lubricants, chemicals, expendable parts, spare parts,
                        supplies or any other requirements that are necessary for the safe operation
                        of the ship;

after the expiration of the appropriate period of time specified in
                    subsection (4)(a) for the serving of a notice of objection;
                    or

the information or document is disclosed to a person who would have been
                    empowered under this Regulation to request that it be provided or
                    produced;

the Security Council document S/2012/235;
                (L.N. 140 of
                    2012)

